    "actor_description": "There's a spark here-bright, not desperate-and I want to play with it. I catch myself holding eye contact a beat too long, letting the pause do the work. The heat in me feels easy, almost funny, like I've got room to tease instead of needing to take. I want to test the distance: lean in, back off, watch what it does to them. My smile keeps slipping out on its own, and my voice wants to soften-hooking words, making them land like a touch.",
    "description_text": "{actor} watches with a mischievous steadiness-glances that linger, then slip away like bait. They angle closer, then drift back, leaving space that feels deliberate. A half-smile tugs at their mouth, and their posture stays open and inviting, like they're daring someone to step into the game.",
